  "market_context": "Daily chart showed a bearish reversal candle (open-high-low-close with large lower wick) on Mon 29 Apr 24, following an earlier aggressive move up. The 15-minute chart captured the intraday formation of that reversal and subsequent continuation lower into the New York session.",
  "key_observation": "The daily bearish reversal candle formed when price moved up to create the wick, then reversed sharply to close below its open—confirmed on the 15-minute chart as an open-high-low-close sequence with the close below open.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Analyst identified the daily candle on CL1! (Mon 29 Apr 24) as a bearish reversal candle due to large lower wick and close below open after an initial upward move.",
    "Step 2: Analyst examined the 15-minute chart to verify the lower-time-frame structure: price opened, moved higher (forming the wick), then reversed decisively lower to close below the open.",
    "Step 3: Analyst noted the continuation lower after the reversal candle, including a sweep of prior highs near equilibrium and displacement lower during the New York session.",
    "Step 4: Analyst confirmed the pattern aligns with the open-high-low-close bearish directional sequence expected after a reversal, using the 15-minute chart to validate the daily candle’s formation."
  ],
  "outcome": null,
  "lessons": "A daily bearish reversal candle is confirmed when price moves up to form the wick then closes below open; the 15-minute chart must show the same OHLC sequence. Continuation lower is anticipated once the reversal is validated and aligned with HTF bias.",
